TheRock's iree-libs/CMakeLists.txt sets -DFUSILLI_PLUGIN_SKIP_TESTS=ON when
THEROCK_BUILD_TESTING is off, but fusilli-provider/CMakeLists.txt always
calls enable_testing() and add_subdirectory(test). The integration test
binaries link against libhipdnn_backend.so but do not carry an rpath to
elfutils, so gtest_discover_tests fails at build time when it tries to
exec the freshly linked test binary (libelf.so.1 not found). Honor the
skip flag so we don't build the test tree at all when tests are disabled.

--- a/rocm-libraries/dnn-providers/fusilli-provider/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/rocm-libraries/dnn-providers/fusilli-provider/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -130,5 +130,7 @@ install(TARGETS ${FUSILLI_PLUGIN_TARGET}
 )

 # Tests
-enable_testing()
-add_subdirectory(test)
+if(NOT FUSILLI_PLUGIN_SKIP_TESTS)
+    enable_testing()
+    add_subdirectory(test)
+endif()
